00>(10/7/03 1:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=721.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Aug Acuity Thoughts</span><hr size=1> With the new changes to our shouts I was considering getting Aug Acuity as my next RA.  My thinking is the larger mana pool and damage increase that it gives would help my dps more than just about any other RA I might choose otherwise...<br>
<br>
I currently have:<br>
<br>
IP, Purge, MoPain2, LW, AoMagic, FA2, Aug Dex2<br>
<br>
Other thoughts I had were to look at toughness or AoMagic2 or aug str for the added weapon skill<br>
<br>
<br>
Thoughts?<br>
<br>
Grnok  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=loka@teamskald>Loka</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 20<br> <font color=#ff0000>(10/8/03 6:35 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=721.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Aug Acuity Thoughts</span><hr size=1> Get MoPain 3 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=berdoon>Berdoon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#ff0000>(10/8/03 7:27 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=721.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Aug Acuity Thoughts</span><hr size=1> I would get moparry first, I have moparry 2 and parried two shield slams in a duel against a hero the other day and beat him handily. <p>Berdoon 50Skald Igraine 7xx Weapons Smith<br>
GM Deus Mors</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=connorrowynsun>Connor Rowynsun</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 20<br> <font color=#ff0000>(10/8/03 9:02 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=721.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Aug Acuity Thoughts</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Get MoPain 3<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--> <br>
<br>
Why?<br>
<br>
Its about a 2.5% increase in your overall melee damage over time at a cost of 6 points.  Aug Aucuity 1 increases your DD damage by a similar percentage at a cost of 1 point and given the reduced impact of AoM and Empty Mind on resists, the new higher level DD's and the reduced DD timer, its an even better value now. <p>Jund Bloodaxe - 50th RR 5.9 Berserker - Palomides<br>
Hammer Tyme - 50th RR 4.1 Skald - Palomides<br>
Syf Stormcrow - 50th RR 3.6 Huntress - Palomides<br>
<br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=etherag>Etherag</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 14<br> <font color=#ff0000>(10/8/03 10:34 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=721.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Aug Acuity Thoughts</span><hr size=1> Aug Acuity is one RA that I don’t think gets taken enough.  It’s the only way to raise your charisma other than level and items (there are no +charisma buffs).  As it adds to our power pool, damage cap and overall damage for DDs I wish I had mine even higher.  The only reason I can think of not to get it is if you are a 50 weapon spec and have little use for the DDs, even then I think you are missing out. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=etherag>Etherag</A> at: 10/8/03 10:45 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=narg@teamskald>Narg</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#ff0000>(10/8/03 12:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=721.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Aug Acuity Thoughts</span><hr size=1> If your thinking 50 bs i'd say Aug Acuity would be a must... sorta like increasing Str and adding Mopain if your high weapon.<br>
<br>
I'm still uncertain of what I will do... My spec at 46/46 seems to be alright.<br>
<br>
Are we fixed? dunno.. time will tell.. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=clapperoth>Clapperoth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Fervent</span><br>  Posts: 109<br> <font color=#ff0000>(10/8/03 12:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=721.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Aug Acuity Thoughts</span><hr size=1> For the increase in damage, MoPain 3 would be 6 pts.  For 6 pts you could get Aug Acuity I, Aug Str I, and still have 4 pts left for either level 2 of either of those, or MoParry 1 and 2.  <br>
<br>
My next spare point is going to Aug Acuity 1.  For 1 pt, you will get at least 12-15 extra damage each DD round (possibly more next patch).  Over a battle, with the new timer, that may add up to 50-75 more damage over a fight for just 1 pt. <p>Clapperoth Liefarg<br>
Guild Officer<br>
Rune<br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gisborne>gisborne</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Fervent</span><br>  Posts: 365<br> <font color=#ff0000>(10/8/03 9:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=721.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Aug Acuity Thoughts</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>&quot;Its about a 2.5% increase in your overall melee damage over time &quot;</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Actually it's just a 1.25% increase in RvR.<br>
<br>
1-50% crits, average 25%.<br>
25%*5%=1.25%<br>
<br>
Heck it's even very slightly less than that because that is just an increase over base damage, not total melee damage including crits.<br>
 <p>Eka, lvl 50 skald Percival</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=connorrowynsun>Connor Rowynsun</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 21<br> <font color=#ff0000>(10/9/03 7:54 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=721.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Aug Acuity Thoughts</span><hr size=1> Yar, my bad.  I calculated the increase in damage a crit does to overall damage without the benefit of Master of Pain 1.<br>
<br>
The actual increase in damage that MoPain 1 confers over time is 1.22% and the increase MoPain 2 confers over MoPain 1 is 1.21%.<br>
<br>
In any event, MoPain 1 is a solid buy, MoPain 2 might be a solid enough buy at high realm rank when you're struggling to find things to buy that are of use.  MoPain 3, at 6 pts, is not imo. <p>Jund Bloodaxe - 50th RR 5.9 Berserker - Palomides<br>
Hammer Tyme - 50th RR 4.2 Skald - Palomides<br>
Syf Stormcrow - 50th RR 3.6 Huntress - Palomides<br>
